## Idea 2: AI Integration Packages

**Market Context:** 70% of businesses are implementing or planning AI integration, but 37% cite lack of in-house expertise as the key barrier.

> Source: [GM Insights](https://www.gminsights.com/industry-analysis/enterprise-llm-market)

### Productized AI Services

#### Package A: AI Customer Service Bot

**Fixed Deliverable:** Custom chatbot for website FAQ and lead qualification

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Price | $2,500 setup + $199/mo maintenance |
| Timeline | 2 weeks |
| Includes | Custom training, 3 integrations, monthly tuning |

**Target:** Small businesses spending too much on support

#### Package B: AI Content Pipeline

**Fixed Deliverable:** Automated content generation workflow

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Price | $3,500 setup + $299/mo |
| Timeline | 3 weeks |
| Includes | Custom prompts, brand voice training, editorial workflow |

**Target:** Marketing teams overwhelmed with content demands

#### Package C: AI Document Processing

**Fixed Deliverable:** Automated extraction from invoices, contracts, or forms

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Price | $5,000-15,000 depending on complexity |
| Timeline | 4-8 weeks |
| Includes | Custom model training, integration, validation rules |

**Target:** Operations teams drowning in manual data entry

### Viability Assessment

| Factor | Assessment |
|--------|------------|
| Viability | High |
| Effort | Medium (requires systemization) |
| Revenue | $50K-150K/yr |
| Moat | Expertise + process |

### Why Productize AI Services?

**Problems with Custom AI Projects:**
- Hard to scope (client doesn't know what they need)
- Unlimited scope creep
- Difficult to price accurately
- Every project starts from scratch

**Productized Benefits:**
- Clear deliverable, clear price
- Repeatable process = efficiency
- Easier to sell (no complex scoping)
- Can hire/train others to deliver

